  "doc_id": "37910",
  "text": "The internal consistency among the reviewers was calculated using IBM SPSS software (IBM Corp., Armonk, NY, USA). When undeterminable responses were included in a question, the question was excluded for the reliability statistics. The Fisher-Freeman-Halton exact test was performed using the EZR software program (Jichi Medical University Saitama Medical Center, Japan) [CITATION_1] . The other statistical analyses were performed using IBM SPSS software. With the nonparametric Mann- Whitney U test, the null hypothesis was \"the distribution of ratings for the two groups is the same\". A p-value of < 0.05 was considered to be statistically significant.",
